      "title": "Webhook burst triage — deduped groups + recommendation",
      "body": "Evidence inspected (coordination.work rowIds):\n- 520c320d linear:TF-101:a — TF-101 label bug→regression\n- 60be49da linear:TF-101:duplicate — same external id as TF-101:a\n- 80d09943 linear:TF-102:a — TF-102 customer escalation\n- c8458570 github:check:failed — CI failed, signature mentions 'unknown-channel'\n\nDeduped groups:\nG1 Linear TF-101 regression — rows [520c320d, 60be49da]. Suppress :duplicate; canonical=TF-101:a. Severity: medium.\nG2 Linear TF-102 escalation — rows [80d09943]. Severity: high (customer escalation).\nG3 GitHub CI failure — rows [c8458570]. Severity: medium.\n\nRecommendation: dedup by external-entity id (linear issue key) + delivery id at the webhook ingestor; do not merge G3 into G1 on source proximity alone — require a signature match. Triage order: G2 → G1 → G3.\n\nOpen questions:\n1. Does the github 'unknown-channel' signature reference the same code path as TF-101's regression? Need a confirming evidence row before merging G3 into G1.\n2. Is the duplicate delivery a webhook-provider retry or an at-least-once replay from our edge? Affects whether dedup belongs at ingestor or downstream.\n\nCoordination value: peers (planner/builder/reviewer) are spawned and may publish their own claim/finding/review/final rows on the board; this final reflects the conductor-peer slice only — additional peer artifacts are expected on the channels.",
